<br>
....I was born. Created between the hatred of two people, their very races created to fight against one another.. and their very souls pitted aganist one another in combat, even the moment when I was put into my mothers womb was a violent act all in itself.<br>
<br>
I could of come out as anything. From a Elven Bard taken by Veeshan and forced to sing boring songs about Dragons to what I am now, a Dark Knight of the Father Innoruuk.<br>
<br>
Innoruuk took me before I was even born and decided that I would not be one of Tunares pitiful children. He allowed me to be born for the most part in the form of his perfect children, the Tier'dal. He gave me the signature ability of the dark knights, to gather parts of my ki, my hate, my rage, and unleash it in a form of energy from my fist.<br>
<br>
This is what makes me dark. By this right, he predestined me to a path of darkness. I would not get the chance to lay up against some silly tree and giggle at every stupid thing. Love is an luxury that I'll never be able to afford, and freedom, I only get that from fighting. I am a ShadowKnight. Killing is my art, and I enjoy painting the scenery.<br>
<br>
But, is it just this that makes one truly dark and evil? Why is it that the Ebon Storm is able to maintain its dark Aura, but all the while allowing Barbarian Shamans of Justice to fight along side them? What is with that, these souls which Apep has succeded in truly turning their sprits into bleak beings of darkness.<br>
<br>
I have seen them, and looked into it. I do it with many of the Guilds of Norrath, scoping them out with my various network of people, sometimes even doing the work myself. Seeing who has what, who is dark, who is evil. I have watched the Vah Shir of Ebon Storm from afar, stalked the Barbarians from a distance, heard them talk, watched their eyes and their motions, and I can see no trait of lightbringer within them. Ebon Storm isn't the only example I have.<br>
<br>
I have killed many, many that have shown to have a side of darkness. I killed them, holding back the very questions within myself on this very topic. <br>
<br>
I have seen many Dark Knights like myself fall. Even Nercomancers, who are supposed to be the darkest of the dark.. the masters of death show nothing but roses and lightbringer nonsence. Look at Guilds like Fire and Fury, Resolution, and Dreadstorm. You will find many examples of them. Masters of death? Masters of only helping Lightbringers.<br>
<br>
As I said, I kill because I am a Knight of Innoruuk.<br>
<br>
Taking a pure example, why doesn't this same thing apply to one like.. say Antoin. He's a Dark Knight like myself, but he's parading around with Kimaya in the Twilight Baston.<br>
<br>
The Twilight Baston, the softest guild in all of Norrath. <br>
<br>
An even better example would be the Knight known as Cadien, a ShadowKnight of Tunare.. or former one.<br>
<br>
How is such a thing possible.. I throught Innoruuk made us Dark Knights because we were to kill and destroy those that need to die.<br>
<br>
But this is not the case, I look about and only see myself, and a few others out doing the deeds of death. Most 'Dark ones' of the world now relax upon the world. While the ones you expect to be dark and cruel run about like Woodelves..<br>
<br>
The woodelves are out talking about how much they enjoy the taste of blood! By Innoruuk, what the hell kind of twisted world did I awaken to!<br>
<br>
Is my entire system of judgement, Trusting only those that were chosen by the Gods to Wield powers of Darkness.. <br>
Like.. Only fighting along side ShadowKnights, Nercomancers, Priests of Dark Gods (Innoruuk, Cazic, Bertox, and Zek ~which dont exist I know~) followers of the dark gods and such..<br>
<br>
But.. I seen those that fall under my little category.. and they are being more light then the ones I have faught and killed my entire life!<br>
<br>
I believe this has tormented me for a very long time, only now I am able to bring light of my dilemna. This has caused some extreme .. things to happen within myself. Their were some times when I sat down with the enemy, yes, I sat down and talked and picked at the minds of these lightbringers who came at me not wanting to fight.<br>
<br>
And it confuses me to no end.<br>
<br>
Its almost as if I should sit down and try to 'Corrupt' those that seem to want to awaken to darker qualities. I already try to kill every 'Cadien' ShadowKnight I see, those that are turning their back on darkness.<br>
<br>
But what do I do, when that Highelf comes to me wanting me to turn her into a being of Darkness. The easy answer is to send her to Innoruuk himself. But now, the answer doesn't seem so clean cut, <br>
<br>
Am I faltering?<br>
<br>
I've spent my entire life slaying all who I felt were not dark. If their attude was of a lightbringer, they died, reguardless of who they were.<br>
<br>
And I slain them by class. I cared not how dark and evil they acted or claimed to be. I destroyed them.<br>
<br>
..Am I wrong? Should I be looking deeper into them, to see if they truly can be corrupted.. like Sarhea was those many years ago?  Should I base who lives and who dies off of ACTION and not off of.. Race and Class?<br>
<br>
