<br>
I do not know you, and must admit ignorance to the language your sigil written in.<br>
<br>
As you have posted your message publicly... I will assume you wish a public response.  <br>
<br>
In my humble opinion, you are considering things far to much.  Judging by your words we both serve the same Master... Give yourself to his Will.  Act on his accord, and do not color it with your own opinions.  Be his Fist upon this decrepit world.<br>
<br>
If we stop to consider if every soul we crush beneth our heel.. or every elf we break upon a rack.. is meant to be of the darkness, we will fall into nothing but doubt.  How can we preform our most holy tasks in His name if we doubt ourselves?<br>
<br>
There is truth in your words.. many misuse the gifts He has given them.  They should be put down, they are worse then then Koda'Dal.  Traitors.  As for those who wish to turn to darkness, they must prove themselves.  Should they be given the opportunity, if they fall into our grasp?  Perhaps...  Go with what you feel.<br>
<br>
Do not make such a decision with logic and thought, act with His Will.  If they are worthy He will make it known.  If we kill them are they truely meant to live?  I think not.<br>
<br>
Do not let these doubts plauge you... Remember that with in us burns His Will... and to deny it is blasphemy.<br>
<br>
In service, <br>
<br>
~Vabris Vy'Tok, of House Vy'Tok<br>
