<br>
I mean, its quite obious that he frowns upon the ..well as I put it, those like the Tier'dal who side and guild along those that are with the Twilight Baston.<br>
<br>
What does Innoruuk think of those like Apep, who corrupts all those about him, his Vah Shir Minions or his Barbarian Shamanic Women.<br>
<br>
What does the father see from those who spent their entire lives using all, Tier'dal and lightbringer alike to gain their status of power, the path most females take.<br>
<br>
What does Innoruuk think about the one who takes the Woodelf, and turns him or her from a docile tree hugging bastard into a complete retardation of what Tunare created tehm to be? <br>
<br>
The fact of it is that we really dont't know what Innoruuk wants. I don't fight because Innoruuk commands me, he only commands me that I walk in total and complete Hate.<br>
<br>
I fight because thats all I've known my entire life. Every question I could answer with my sword.. execpt for the reason on why I am still weak while they, as in the rest of them, gain in much power and strenght.<br>
<br>
What am I doing wrong, I wonder.<br>
<br>
What I feel.. I've lost touch of what I feel I think. Its becomming as if I am tiring of fighting, espically now since the battles are no longer ones I can win with my sword. <br>
<br>
The Lightbringers Dominate this world. They grow in power while I am dammed to an existance in my 55th level of power for .. hell I don't know how long.<br>
<br>
But I remember when your words were my words. Back then, when the world was still a battle ground.. I could let my hair down, draw my sword and cleave into some Elvish flesh. <br>
<br>
Damn Norrath, and damn the lightbringers for changing this world to their liking. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.leagueofshadows.net/"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> League Of Shadows</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
For a prisoner, the only true freedom comes from fighting.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bakanome>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 633<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/22/03 6:58:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gods, Classes, and Darkness?</span><hr size=1> I am going to give you the one and only glance into my mind that you will ever see, Shinai.  I see as you do, and quite frankly, it scares me.<br>
<br>
I have spent most of my life fighting creatures of darkest pitch, their hearts sewn with evil beyond redemption.  Even yourself, from time to time.  Now however, things have become...  mired.  The lines are blurred.  I see Vah Shir attacking cities that give them no harm.  High elves, even paladins, simply walking over dead guards and even BEGGING the attackers to allow them to loot weapons from the dead and the dying.  Druids even slaughtering their own charges en masse, all in the name of this accursed balance.  They can justify anything with balance, you know.  It's a universal excuse.<br>
<br>
I know you have seen the same.<br>
<br>
Things are changing, but instead of being a final victory, it is becoming one massive shade of grey, corrupted, power driven.  More evil than anything the darkness could bring. And that, Shinai, leaves people like you, and me, out of luck, and out of time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eveningshadow>EveningShadow</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/22/03 8:43:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gods, Classes, and Darkness?</span><hr size=1> I will admit that I am young, perhaps I have not yet had time to become jaded such as you.  Will I in time?  Perhaps... but I can only remain true to His Will as best as I can.  There is no way to tell what is his Will and what is merely our wantings, we can only do our best to act in perfect Hate.<br>
<br>
As for the others, both the tainted lightbringers and the damned soft Tier'dal who walk with our enemies, we can only act upon what we feel.  If they come before you and are found wanting... cut them down.  If He desires their service, He will return them in some way.<br>
<br>
What are you doing wrong?  I can not answer that.  I can only tell you my observations based on your notes.  You doubt yourself, it seems, because the rewards you wish are not  forthcoming.  We do not always receive the reward we deserve, when we feel we deserve it.  All things come in time, for some it takes longer then others.  Obstacles merely prove dedication, and make us stronger.  I will not sift the blame and say something trite as &quot;His Will bring all things at the time HE wishes,&quot; because it is simply not true.  We make our own path.  There are many diffrent roads to his Will.<br>
<br>
Do as you say you always have done.  Tear through whatever stands between you and where you wish to be.  Rend it asunder with your sword.  Burn it with your touch.  The very fact these things attempt to prevent you from your goals should be reason enough to destroy them.<br>
<br>
Through destruction we will grow, that is the way it has always been.<br>
<br>
<br>
~Vabris Vy'Tok, of House Vy'Tok<br>
Cleric of Innoruuk, Acolyte of Saryrn<br>
